O Phoebe patiens, suyeris retro licet,

Mediaque ruptum merseris caelo diem. Lucan. 4. 282 Substituit merso dum nox sua lumina Phoebo. pallentibus umbris suggests the pale shades of the dead, cf. Verg. Aen. 4. 26 pallentes umbras Erebi. Possibly the writer has in mind the voy- age of the sun-god through the realm of the dead beneath the earth.
